<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="456" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,402,1800]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1159,1185]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Remarks.</emphasis>
According to the most recent revision of the Chinese species of this genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Miroshnikov, A. I. &amp; Lin, M. - Y." pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="177 - 214" refId="ref23895" refString="Miroshnikov, A. I. &amp; Lin, M. - Y. (2017) The Longicorn Beetle Genus Apatophysis Chevrolat, 1860 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Apatophyseini) in China, with Preliminary Remarks on its Intrageneric Structure and with Descriptions of Three New Species. Special Bulletin of the Coleopterological Society of Japan, 1, 177 - 214." type="journal article" year="2017">Miroshnikov &amp; Lin 2017</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gebler" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[229,382,1195,1222]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apatophysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serricornis">
<emphasis box="[229,246,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[259,382,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">serricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in 
<collectingCountry box="[564,631,1195,1221]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[644,744,1195,1221]" country="China" name="Xinjiang Uygur" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Xinjiang</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[796,974,1195,1222]" country="China" name="Nei Mongol" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Inner Mongolia</collectingRegion>
; however, the authors also reported on the two problematic males that are known from one of the southernmost provinces— 
<collectingRegion box="[1080,1212,1231,1258]" country="China" name="Guangdong" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Guangdong</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[1232,1341,1231,1257]" name="Mongolia" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
(mainly southern part of the country) and SE 
<collectingCountry box="[566,700,1267,1293]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,402,1800]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
This highly variable species has been already described several times based on its different forms (
<taxonomicName authority="(Gebler, 1845)" baseAuthorityName="Gebler" baseAuthorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apatophysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tomentosa">
<emphasis box="[1291,1308,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1321,1436,1304,1329]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">tomentosa</emphasis>
(Gebler, 1845)
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="(Motschulsky, 1860)" baseAuthorityName="Motschulsky" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[332,738,1339,1366]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apatophysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obtusicollis">
<emphasis box="[332,349,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[364,493,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">obtusicollis</emphasis>
(Motschulsky, 1860)
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Semenov, 1901" authorityName="Semenov" authorityYear="1901" box="[751,1086,1339,1366]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apatophysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mongolica">
<emphasis box="[751,768,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[783,901,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">mongolica</emphasis>
Semenov, 1901
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Kadlec, 2006" authorityName="Kadlec" authorityYear="2006" box="[1099,1429,1339,1366]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apatophysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kadyrbekovi">
<emphasis box="[1099,1116,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1131,1268,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">kadyrbekovi</emphasis>
Kadlec, 2006
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Danilevsky, M. L." box="[159,355,1375,1401]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="7 - 55" refId="ref21854" refString="Danilevsky, M. L. (2008) Apatophysis Chevrolat, 1860 (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae) of Russia and adjacent regions. Studies and Reports of District Museum Prague-East, Taxonomical Series, 4 (1 - 2), 7 - 55." type="journal article" year="2008">Danilevsky 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Miroshnikov, A. I. &amp; Lin, M. - Y." box="[368,660,1375,1401]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="177 - 214" refId="ref23895" refString="Miroshnikov, A. I. &amp; Lin, M. - Y. (2017) The Longicorn Beetle Genus Apatophysis Chevrolat, 1860 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Apatophyseini) in China, with Preliminary Remarks on its Intrageneric Structure and with Descriptions of Three New Species. Special Bulletin of the Coleopterological Society of Japan, 1, 177 - 214." type="journal article" year="2017">Miroshnikov &amp; Lin 2017</bibRefCitation>
). It also shows a strong sexual dimorphism, which causes additional difficulties in its systematics.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,402,1800]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gebler" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[199,467,1447,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apatophysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serricornis">
<emphasis box="[199,467,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Apatophysis serricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, unlike some other representatives of the genus, is most likely a nocturnal species (at least 
<specimenCount box="[208,373,1483,1510]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
have been recorded as attracted to a light trap by 
<bibRefCitation author="Namhaidorzh, B." box="[916,1158,1483,1509]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="495 - 538" refId="ref24062" refString="Namhaidorzh, B. (1972) On the fauna of longicorn beetles (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae) of the Mongolian People's Republic. Insects of Mongolia, 1, 495 - 538. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1972">Namhaidorzh (1972))</bibRefCitation>
and its bionomy remains largely unknown. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Danilevsky, M. L." box="[504,715,1519,1545]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="7 - 55" refId="ref21854" refString="Danilevsky, M. L. (2008) Apatophysis Chevrolat, 1860 (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae) of Russia and adjacent regions. Studies and Reports of District Museum Prague-East, Taxonomical Series, 4 (1 - 2), 7 - 55." type="journal article" year="2008">Danilevsky (2008)</bibRefCitation>
, it is ecologically associated with desert and semi-desert habitats of different 
<typeStatus box="[284,343,1556,1582]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">types</typeStatus>
(both sandy and clay soils). Larvae develop in roots of probably different desert shrubs and trees, however, development only in 
<taxonomicName authority="Bunge" authorityName="Bunge" box="[506,705,1591,1618]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Haloxylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[506,623,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Haloxylon</emphasis>
Bunge
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[721,899,1591,1618]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Amaranthaceae</taxonomicName>
) was confirmed (
<bibRefCitation author="Danilevsky, M. L." box="[1100,1298,1591,1617]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="125 - 129" refId="ref21672" refString="Danilevsky, M. L. (1988) Subfamily Apatophyseinae. In: Svacha, P. &amp; Danilevsky, M. L. (Eds.), Cerambycoid larvae of Europe and Soviet Union (Coleoptera, Cerambycoidea). Part II. Acta Universitatis Carolinae, Biologica, 31 (3 - 4), 125 - 129." type="journal article" year="1988">Danilevsky 1988</bibRefCitation>
). Adults are active from June to August (
<bibRefCitation author="Danilevsky, M. L." box="[467,665,1627,1653]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="7 - 55" refId="ref21854" refString="Danilevsky, M. L. (2008) Apatophysis Chevrolat, 1860 (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae) of Russia and adjacent regions. Studies and Reports of District Museum Prague-East, Taxonomical Series, 4 (1 - 2), 7 - 55." type="journal article" year="2008">Danilevsky 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,402,1800]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
